# Git Push Policy

NEVER run `git push` automatically.

Always ask the user before pushing:
> "Push করব? (Should I push to GitHub?)"

Only run `git commit` and `git push` when the user **explicitly** says:
- "push করো"
- "push koro"
- "push it"
- "deploy করো"
- or similar clear instruction

`git add` and `git commit` is allowed without asking.
`git push` requires explicit user approval every time.
